# Seasons Images

This folder contains local images for the 72 Japanese micro-seasons.

## Adding Images

Images should be named: `{number}-{romaji-slug}.jpg`
Example: `70-fuki-no-hana-saku.jpg`

### Manual Download Steps

1. Search Wikimedia Commons for the plant/phenomenon
2. Right-click the image and "Save Image As..."
3. Rename to match the naming convention
4. Recommended: resize to 640px width

### Quick Sources

- Butterbur (fuki): https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Petasites_japonicus
- Cherry blossoms: https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Cherry_blossom
- Japanese seasons: https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:Seasons_in_Japan

